# three-dreams — Workspace Context

## Role of This Project

This is the **Phase 4 game fork** — *Three Dreams* — a standalone Vue 3 PWA forked from `BASE/pwa-shell`. It hosts the shipping game loop (menus, `GameLogicModule`, scenes, NPC wiring) while consuming `@base/*` packages from `SHARED/`. First game experience built on the @base platform.

**Current phase: 4B** — Real NPC GLBs wired in scenes 01 and 03 with verified animations.

**Narrative:** Prodigal Son arc. Five scenes across two planes (real world chibi / dream world realistic).

## Ecosystem Topology

```
e:/Projects/
  three-dreams/          ← THIS repo — Vue 3 PWA + Three.js stack
  SHARED/packages/       ← @base/* packages (engine-core, threejs-engine, player-three,
                            scene-builder, camera-three, input, audio)
  BASE/pwa-shell/        ← upstream shell template
  threejs-engine-dev/    ← Phase 3d harness (sibling — Phase 4C blocked on Phase 3d)
```

## Code Placement Rules

- Reusable runtime → `SHARED/packages/` as `@base/*`
- Game rules, narrative, Pinia game state → this repo (`GameLogicModule`, stores, views, scenes)
- Heavy scene authoring / editor tooling → prefer `threejs-engine-dev`; promote stable pieces to SHARED
- Do not edit `@base/*` packages directly from this repo — use pnpm workspace links

## Stack

Vue 3 · TypeScript strict · Tailwind CSS · Vue Router · Pinia · Vite · Vitest
Three.js · `@base/threejs-engine` · `@base/player-three` · `@base/scene-builder` · `@base/camera-three` · `@base/input` · `@base/audio`
Game: `GameLogicModule` · `useGameStore` · scene registry (`scenes/registry.ts`) · `SceneGameplayPolicy`
